text: Nizhny Tashbukan () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Tashbukanovsky Selsoviet, Gafuriysky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 166 as of 2010. There are 4 streets. == Geography == It is located 24 km from Krasnousolsky. == References == Category:Rural localities in Gafuriysky District
title: Nizhny Tashbukan
